In early 1970s she sang numerous advertising jingles including the 1971 Coca-Cola commercial I'd Like to Teach the World to Sing.
In 1974, she was a background vocalist on Eddie Floyd's album, "Soul Street".
In 1975, McCullough relocated from Detroit to New York City to continue her career as a background singer.
In 1979 McCullough began a solo career and recorded three albums: Love Zone (1979), Ullanda McCullough (1981) and Watching You Watching Me (1982).
